It's the kind of vacation
where I get a job?

01:15:39.200 --> 01:15:42.042
He needs to leave tonight. It would
take a couple of days

01:15:42.068 --> 01:15:44.665
to get down there but we could all get
to know each other better in the car.

01:15:44.720 --> 01:15:46.735
You realized that's insane, right?

01:15:46.761 --> 01:15:49.465
Right, that's probably
part of the appeal.

01:15:51.600 --> 01:15:54.368
Remember when you told me
that you and dad were done?

01:15:54.394 --> 01:15:56.403
Oh actually no, wait.
That's was today!

01:15:56.429 --> 01:15:56.930
No... no!

01:15:57.000 --> 01:16:00.123
This is not about me and your dad.

01:16:00.125 --> 01:16:02.112
No, so what's this about?
Because it's not about

01:16:02.138 --> 01:16:04.170
me working in a professional kitchen.

01:16:04.200 --> 01:16:07.000
- It'll be fun.
- Mom, stop! We're not doing this.

01:16:07.080 --> 01:16:09.759
You're not the one who decides.
I'm the mom and you're the kid.

01:16:09.760 --> 01:16:10.905
Based on what?

01:16:11.000 --> 01:16:12.830
Your great sense of
responsibilities or

01:16:12.831 --> 01:16:14.625
your amazing problem solving skills?

01:16:14.680 --> 01:16:17.022
You want us to move
to Puerto Vallarta with

01:16:17.023 --> 01:16:17.988
some stranger from what, God knows...

01:16:17.989 --> 01:16:19.545
No! He's not a stranger!

01:16:19.600 --> 01:16:23.872
Lucy, please!
I have to know, I have to do this!

01:16:23.873 --> 01:16:26.408
Have to know what?
How awesome your life

01:16:26.409 --> 01:16:27.585
would've been if I hadn't been born?

01:16:27.640 --> 01:16:33.080
God, no! No, Lucy, you're the only
thing that's turned out right.

01:16:34.120 --> 01:16:37.400
You're... everything!

01:16:40.560 --> 01:16:45.840
I just... I just can't do it anymore.

01:16:45.920 --> 01:16:50.080
Can't do what? Be my mom?

01:16:51.360 --> 01:16:53.200
I just...

01:16:54.480 --> 01:16:58.240
... feel like I'm... like I'm dying.

01:16:59.640 --> 01:17:01.440
I...

01:17:04.000 --> 01:17:08.680
I need something.
I need... something else.

01:17:11.840 --> 01:17:15.280
I need to... belong.

01:17:16.600 --> 01:17:20.440
I need to find something.

01:17:24.120 --> 01:17:26.520
Okay, mom.

01:17:30.800 --> 01:17:34.160
If you need to go... go.

01:17:38.640 --> 01:17:43.800
- I can't go without you.
- I'm 16. I'm not pregnant.

01:17:43.880 --> 01:17:46.040
I'm not getting married.

01:17:48.200 --> 01:17:50.670
Who can take better
care of me than me?

01:17:50.671 --> 01:17:53.442
No, Lucy, I...

01:17:54.290 --> 01:17:55.519
You're gonna make me run
away to Mexico

01:17:55.520 --> 01:17:58.825
with you and your
high school boyfriend? No!

01:18:00.360 --> 01:18:02.440
You go.

01:18:11.080 --> 01:18:15.680
I... I can maybe go for two weeks.

01:18:17.600 --> 01:18:19.880
I'll take it.

01:18:20.000 --> 01:18:23.480
- I'll give you the ATM card.
- Okay.

01:18:25.520 --> 01:18:29.440
- Okay, two weeks.
- Okay.

01:18:35.520 --> 01:18:38.624
<i>Jean Paul Satre said we experience
sense of being abandon</i>

01:18:38.650 --> 01:18:41.505
<i>when we realize there is no God.</i>

01:18:41.560 --> 01:18:45.040
<i>- Or in this case parents to guide us.</i>
- I love you.

01:18:45.880 --> 01:18:48.472
But it forces us to
take absolute responsibility

01:18:48.473 --> 01:18:50.945
for our actions and choices.

01:18:52.080 --> 01:18:53.920
I think I'm responsible.

01:18:55.200 --> 01:18:58.840
You're the most responsible
person that I know.

01:18:58.920 --> 01:19:03.080
Well, you don't know that many people.
- Still, I know a lots of people.

01:19:05.840 --> 01:19:10.360
- Did you hear me before?
- I did.

01:19:13.240 --> 01:19:14.840
Thanks for having my back.

01:19:16.680 --> 01:19:18.760
Always have.

01:19:20.200 --> 01:19:22.360
<i>Always will.</i>

01:19:34.600 --> 01:19:39.160
Please don't hate me for this.
I'll call you everyday.

01:19:49.840 --> 01:19:51.402
My dad will be back in an hour, so...

01:19:51.403 --> 01:19:53.905
- So I'm sure you would have to meet..
- Yeah, I'll be back in here.

01:24:01.880 --> 01:24:04.280
Hi, I'm Lucy Diamond.

01:24:05.880 --> 01:24:08.160
My name is Gerald.

01:24:08.240 --> 01:24:11.320
My mom's the one who ran
away to Mexico with your son.

01:24:12.400 --> 01:24:15.520
Yeah, that kind of circle
back around, didn't it?

01:24:16.840 --> 01:24:19.560
- Are you hungry?
- What are we serving?

01:24:21.920 --> 01:24:26.280
Eggs in hell. Oh, no offense,
it's just custom sauce.

01:24:26.360 --> 01:24:28.280
None taken.

01:24:40.440 --> 01:24:42.785
Actually saw this place
on the food network.

01:24:42.786 --> 01:24:44.225
- Really?
- Yeah.

01:24:45.120 --> 01:24:49.920
Well, we do okay for a food cafe
stuck out in the middle of nowhere.

01:25:05.000 --> 01:25:09.840
Nicely done. The Jalape√±o doesn't
overpower the other flavours.

01:25:09.920 --> 01:25:14.400
This is like a... plate of
home-cooked Americana.

01:25:16.200 --> 01:25:18.080
Cool.

01:25:21.320 --> 01:25:24.400
You know, if you like this,
I make a mean risotto.

01:25:24.835 --> 01:25:25.994
- Oh, I love risotto.
- Yeah.

01:25:26.134 --> 01:25:27.450
It's comfort food.

01:25:30.680 --> 01:25:33.169
<i>Here's how I think my
bigger life will look.</i>

01:25:33.195 --> 01:25:35.745
<i>My parents split up.</i>

01:25:35.800 --> 01:25:38.840
<i>I graduated from the
culinary institute.</i>

01:25:39.640 --> 01:25:44.240
<i>Kenny gets a PhD in something brainy
and world changing.</i>

01:25:44.320 --> 01:25:46.680
<i>Later I publish
a best-selling cookbook</i>

01:25:46.681 --> 01:25:49.785
<i>based on the recipes
from my restaurant.</i>

